'''Lucio Lombardo-Radice''' ([[Catania]], 10 July 1916; [[Bruxelles]], 21 November 1982) was an [[Italy|Italian]] [[mathematician]]. A student of [[Gaetano Scorza]],<ref>{{mathgenealogy|id=97474|name= Lucio Lombardo Radice}}</ref> Lombardo-Radice contributed to [[finite geometry]] and [[geometric combinatorics]] together with [[Guido Zappa]] and [[Beniamino Segre]], and wrote important works concerning the [[Non-Desarguesian plane]]. He was also a leading member of the [[Italian Communist Party]] and a member of its central committee.<ref>{{citation|title=Eurocommunism: its roots and future in Italy and elsewhere|first=George R.|last=Urban|publisher=Universe Books|year=1978|isbn=978-0-87663-329-8|page=279}}.</ref>
The Istituto Tecnico Statale Commerciale "Lucio Lombardo Radice" per Programmatori, a school in [[Rome, Italy]], founded in 1982 as the XXV Istituto Tecnico Commerciale per Programmatori, was in 1992 renamed after Lombardo-Radice. It is now name Istituto di Istruzione Superiore Lombardo Radice<ref>[http://www.islombardoradice.gov.it/dinamico/312/home/scuola.html Brief history of ITC Lucio Lombardo Radice] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090805072317/http://www.itclombardoradice.roma.scuolaeservizi.it/scuola.htm |date=2009-08-05 }}.</ref>
